abstract: The rate would be raised in an effort to slow inflation, but Fed policy makers have not agreed to a timetable for the move, documents show.
snippet: The rate would be raised in an effort to slow inflation, but Fed policy makers have not agreed to a timetable for the move, documents show.
lead_paragraph: Federal Reserve policy makers expect to eventually raise their benchmark interest rate in an effort to slow inflation, but they have not agreed to a timetable for the move, according to minutes of the Fed’s last meeting in early August.

headline.main: Fed Hints It Will Raise Benchmark Interest Rate
